      "writtenOn": "2026-02-03T17:59:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e There will be different build targets like:\n\u003e * high-availability (which will not pack any of these libraries in the plugin jar)\n\u003e * high-availability-pubsub-gcp (which will include the GCP client libs)\n\u003e * high-availability-pubsub-aws (which will include the AWS SNS+SQS client libs)\n\nDifferent libraries may have different requirements that may have different API syntax. Having different build targets isn\u0027t enough; you would need to fork the code.\n\nOr, you create a generic API (e.g. events-forwarder) and create multiple modules that implement that API in different code with different builds.\n\n\u003e In the end, if *really* needed, we may do a similar thing like you did with the events broker: we may move the core of the high-availability plugin into a module and provide concrete implementations in plugins.\n\nExactly, this looks like a duplication effort to me.",
